'''Snowtroopers''' were [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] trained to operate in arctic climates. Some snowtroopers were deployed under [[Death Squadron/Legends|Death Squadron's]] [[Blizzard Force/Legends|Blizzard Force]], as well as other arctic forces.

==History==
[[File:Snowtrooper_Vanguard_AoEB.png|thumb|left|250px|Snowtroopers storm Echo Base on Hoth]]
Snowtroopers were utilized on many different icy worlds, including the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Garrison/Legends|garrison]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Akuria II]]. Their most notable conquest was at the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], where the Imperial [[Blizzard Force/Legends|Blizzard Force]] defeated the forces of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] and overran [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]].<ref name="GG3">''[[Galaxy Guide 3: The Empire Strikes Back]]''</ref> The Rebel general in charge of Echo Base, [[Carlist Rieekan/Legends|Carlist Rieekan]], later reflected that the snowtroopers just stepped right in to assault the base fully equipped, when the Rebel Alliance had had to spend months trying to prep their gear for the winter conditions on the planet.<ref name="Imperial Handbook">''[[Star Wars: Imperial Handbook: A Commander's Guide]]''</ref>

One of the first missions involving the snowtroopers was the surprise Imperial assault on the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] founders on [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]]. [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] had tracked his [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] apprentice [[Galen Marek]] to the planet, in a secret plot to both capture the would-be founders of the rebellion and destroy Marek. Snowtroopers stormed the shelter atop the snowy mountain, quickly wiping out [[Rahm Kota/Legends|Rahm Kota's]] guards.

A unit of 10 snowtroopers, called [[Baker Company (snowtrooper)|Baker Company]], were [[Mission to Goratak III|deployed]] to [[Goratak III]] to recover an Imperial [[I2-CG droid/Legends|I2-CG]] [[storage and transceiving droid]] before the Rebel Alliance could find it. The contingent was led by a bounty hunter named [[Feskitt Bobb]].

Later, in [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]], a unit of snowtroopers [[Battle of Pallaxides|fought]] for the [[Imperial Remnant]] on the planet [[Pallaxides]] against the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]].

==Equipment==
[[File:SnowtrooperChestplate-SWBC21.png|thumb|right|180px|A snowtrooper breastplate]]

===Armor===
[[Snowtrooper armor/Legends|Snowtrooper armor]] was well suited to the climate extremes of frozen worlds such as [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]], [[Rhen Var/Legends|Rhen Var]], and [[Toola/Legends|Toola]]. Unlike other troopers, snowtroopers wore a white, rugged [[Body glove/Legends|body glove]], which provided camouflage, and provided thermal insulation from the cold. Over this was an eighteen-piece outer shell altered to include more powerful heating and personal environment units, and an airtight fabric oversuit for additional protection from the cold. To facilitate breathing in extremely cold or dangerous atmospheres, a breather hood enveloped the snowtrooper's faceplate and fed into the suit liner. Each trooper was equipped with terrain-grip boots, a standard utility belt containing high-tension wire, [[Grappling hook/Legends|grappling hooks]], ion [[Flare/Legends|flares]], additional [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] ammunition, a survival kit, and ration packs.<ref name="GG3" /> Their tents and other equipment was supplied by the company [[Garlostar]]. Their breastplate resembled that of a [[Krail Armory]] [[Model 1010 Photo-reactive Personal Armor]].

[[File:Snowtrooper_Helmet.jpg|thumb|left|180px|A snowtrooper's helmet]]
Their helmets had built-in polarized snow goggles. The breastplate worn by the snowtroopers was constructed of a [[Plastoid/Legends|plastoid]] composite armor. Near the center were all of the controls for the completely self-sufficient troopers' life-support systems. These included an external temperature monitor, power cell monitor, and the controls for the suit's heater. The troopers' backpacks housed the main heating unit, main power cell, communications unit, and a [[Homing beacon/Legends|homing beacon]]. The pack also had the ability to work as a power source for other equipment. Snowtroopers could survive up to two weeks in even the harshest frozen environments on their internal suit power and supplies. They also wore white heated pants with pockets.<ref name="Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary]]''</ref>

===Weaponry===
Snowtroopers were armed with the standard-issue [[E-11 blaster rifle/Legends|E-11 blaster rifles]] of stormtroopers,<ref name="GG3" /> [[SE-14r light repeating blaster/Legends|SE-14r light repeating blasters]], two [[Concussion grenade/Legends|concussion grenades]],<ref name="GG3" /> and one [[Fragmentation grenade/Legends|fragmentation grenade]]. Elite snowtroopers were given the [[DLT-20A blaster rifle/Legends|DLT-20A blaster rifle]] as a replacement for the E-11,<ref name="Rebel Storm">{{SWMiniCite|set=Rebel Storm|pack=Elite Snowtrooper}}</ref> and two [[Stun grenade/Legends|stun grenades]]. Snowtroopers commonly employed [[E-Web heavy repeating blaster/Legends|E-Web heavy repeating blasters]].<ref name="Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary" />

==Behind the scenes==
In ''[[Assault on Hoth]]'', snowtroopers are divided into two categories as part of the game mechanics: light snowtroopers and heavy snowtroopers, the former operating on foot and the latter operating an E-Web heavy repeating blaster.

